    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-07-06T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-07-06T13:00:00-05:00" n="19"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d19">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.24/55: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wright</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-07-06T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >July 6, 1939—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 3:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>71. Your circular telegram of June 27, 7 p.m. Secretary of State, as well as the
                    Secretary of National Defense and Colonel Batista<note n="6" xml:id="d19fn6"
                        >Fulgencia Batista, Chief of Staff, Cuban Army.</note>
                    <pb facs="0016" n="10" xml:id="pg_10"/> to both of whom the Secretary of State
                    referred me and the latter of whom has been absent but whom I have now seen,
                    express themselves as wholly in sympathy with the purposes of the resolution,
                    the points of which as enumerated in the Department’s telegram I have discussed
                    with them in some detail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wright</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
